< Text>
Normally I always listen to the ratings so I wasn‚Äôt expecting great service. I‚Äôve had a lot of trouble getting my medications but the pharmacy staff have been wonderful at working with me through the difficulties getting things authorized by the insurance. I felt very cared about there and I noticed they do the same for many others. I feel like rather than telling me there was nothing they could do and was not their problem (disconnected like so many are today), they actually took the time to call my doctor, talk to my insurance, and try to get everything all sorted out. Even if the rules were blocking me from getting me the medication I needed, they allowed me a few until everything got sorted through so I didn‚Äôt have to miss a dose. They are human and in a world full of beurocracy, this was a welcome surprise.<//Text>

< Review>
Got a text about  11:00 saying RX was ready .About 5pm I went to pickup antibiotics for my granddaughter who had been discharged just that morning from emergency room.Many customers ahead of me and  after waiting in line for 15 -20 min. I was told by a pharmacist assistant that Doctor had made a mistake on RX and she needed to call him. I told her we needed the RX filled because Granddaughter  was in pain and she stated that she couldn't be in pain because she had been given pain meds that morning. (Implying that Granddaughter should be popping pain pills)
We asked for RX back so we could go elsewhere which is when she realized that
Doctor had faxed over a revised RX but that one had been filed away without being filled.
After waiting another 10 min I was given the the pills but not before being told that if that ever happened again I would have to wait the usual waiting time (which could be hours.) Seems mistakes happen often at this pharmacy!
I told her this was their mistake not mine and she proceeded to tell me to next time go to another store.
Mind you not once did she ever make eye contact with me . The whole time she proceeded to talk at me not with me.
She was not only unprofessional and rude but you could tell she was frazzled
by how busy it gets.
She definitely needs to get another job where she has no customer contact because after reading the other reviews I can see this behavior is being tolerated by the store.</Review>

<Text>My friends and I came here from out of state and were expecting really great things from a restaurant in Beverly hills. We had very high hopes and it turned out the food here was subpar if you can really consider it that even. The enchiladas were ordered by 3 of us and all 3 of us could not stomach eating it. The food was atrocious and the busboy or server came and was cleaning up and never even bothered to ask how the food was before picking up our plates that were obviously full of food not even eaten. The waiter then came to find only one of the 3 enchilada entrees was still left to be picked up by a busboy or server. And asked the golden question " Was everything good?" My friends and I all informed him that we were unhappy with the meal and he decided to offer compensation for only one of the enchilada meals even though all 3 of us literally ate a bite or so of it. So I was punished by paying for food that was no where near the level of where it should be considering the area the restaurant was at. Had the busboy or server did their job and informed the chef or waiter of the fact that none of us actually ate the food then we wouldn't have been stuck paying for food that we all disliked. <username>Beauty Undercover< /username><Pics>None< /Pics><review>WORST CINCO EVER!
In anticipation of celebrating Cinco de Mayo this evening, I placed a to-go order this afternoon to avoid the 5pm rush.  I ordered 5 entrees, sides, dessert, etc. with a lovely lady and told her I would pick everything up at 6:15 pm.  When I arrived at the restaurant it was TOTAL CHAOS.  There was no organization as to which person was "next" in the queue and from the outside I could see bags of food placed all over the interior of the restaurant.  People were literally grazing from bag to bag, touching the exteriors, reaching into the inside, etc. There was a man at the register allowing the craziness to continue.  It took me between 15-20 minutes to reach him and when I asked for my order he told me that there was no order.  I explained that I had spoken with a lady earlier in the day; he emphatically claimed that there was "no woman" at the restaurant and that I must have confused the restaurant with another Frida several blocks away.  30 minutes after I parked, I had to jump in the car and, again, wait in line for someone to greet me.  At the other Frida (Cantina) there was no record of my order and, after closer inspection of the menu, I realized that it could not have been correct restaurant.  I repeatedly called the "right" restaurant on my way to Chipotle (what other choice did I have after 7pm on Cinco de Mayo??)  and was sent straight to voicemail.  When I arrived home I immediately checked my credit card statement ... there it was, charge for $169.13 from the Frida Restaurant on South Beverly Drive!  I called and called again and nobody would answer!!!!  NEVER AGAIN!!!</review><Rating>1< /Rating><Date>1588734591491</Date></record></dataset><record>

< Review>
The price was higher than what I was quoted initially. I needed a kitchen faucet replaced. The receptionist was very friendly, said there would be no charge for coming out. However the technician said if he had to look at the issue, there would be a charge. Kind of conflicting as to what the receptionist communicated.
The day the tech gave a quote, I asked what type of faucet would be a good fit. He recommended buying any other brand than the one I had. I purchased a PriceFister.
After the install the technician said the charge is higher because of the type of faucet and that he had to apply caulking around to seal.
Isn't that what an install involves??? Not happy!!
I chose this company because of the convenience to my home but next time going to go with someone else.< /Review>

<Review>Nicest upscale bar on the strip. Hands down. Beautiful pool area with great views, seating and/or cabanas depending on what time of day or year you come. Either way, it's great. If you're looking to impress on a first date, you will not fail here. If it doesn't impress, say I had a great day/evening and move on. Four different areas, all connected but with completely separate and distinct vibes. All great. Excellent cocktail, wine and bubbles selection at the bar above the pool. DJs and pool parties held here often. This is technically not a rooftop bar however it is roofless on good days and it is elevated 2-3 stories. Though only the elite stay and hang out here, everyone is welcome. Highly recommended anytime of the day, year-round.< /Review>< Time>

< text>
It started off okay when I looked into getting a used car here. After the main contact person, Wesley got too busy to respond to my emails,  I went into the actual store and met with his counter part Sergik. He was way better with emails and contact info. Insisted that the car have a full bmw prep and did a full inspection. A few days before the busy Christmas and new years season, I arranged for the car to be picked up by me. I was coming from 60 miles away so I needed the car to have no issues. Picking it up was easy enough. On my drive home, I realized the cars steering wheel would need to be turned to the left to keep the car straight.  I figured they would fix any alignment issues when they said they would give me new tires and when they did that bmw inspection.  I, also, noticed during that drive home, the car would shake at a stop a little than I expected and heard a small crackling noise from the front driver side. It still drove okay so I figured I'd just check it out after the holiday season since I was so busy.

The first business day after the new years,  I took the car straight to a alignment and mechanic shop and the first thing they tell me that the car had some major suspension issues. Issues I was NOT told about prior and I felt the BMW techs should have caught it before giving me the car. They said it had a lower control arm bushing that were broken on both sides and that my front struts were leaking badly. Unsafe to drive and would cost me over $2,000 to fix for all 4 wheels. I was not happy to hear this and emailed Sergik about it the same day. He only forwarded my response to his conditioning team but never did more. Almost like he didn't care to follow up or say sorry they missed such a huge issue. Only wanted to make the sale. I'm still waiting for a reply from the conditioning team at this BMW but I'm not hopeful they would step up anyways since it's been over a week since I picked up the car. Beware buyers. I had so many bmws in the past but never ran into this issue from a dealer. Sad.<//text>

Initially contacted Valencia BMW through True Car.  The salesperson was professional and courteous.  We negotiated over the phone and I brought my own financing, however Valencia BMW were able to beat my credit unions interest rate, so I went with BMW Finance.   When I arrived at the dealer, I was treated well.  The salesperson and finance manager were professional and accommodated my concerns and answered all my questions.  The reason Valencia BMW is getting three stars rather than five is due to problems with the certified 2017 BMW 750i I purchased, with only 20k miles.   Once the transaction was completed and I drove off the lot, the "Active Driving Assistant" error lights/alerts went off on my screen.  I drove the car back immediately and the salesperson told me service was closed (it was Sunday) and to take the vehicle to my local BMW dealer for service.   I took my 2017 BMW 750i to my local BMW dealer two days later.   Later that afternoon I received a call letting me know there are issues with the "Active Driving Assistant" which they will fix, however they discovered several leaks, including a leak in the transmission.   The latest information was quite disturbing, considering I purchased a "Certified BMW".   I thought the whole idea of purchasing a "Certified BMW" is that they went through a detailed and comprehensive ordeal to certify the car.    How could they miss the issues with the "Active Driving Assistance" and especially leaks, which my local BMW dealer discovered immediately??   The three star review is very gracious, considering many people are less tolerant and would have given them a one star review.   My "Certified BMW" is still in service (three days later) waiting for repairs to be completed.  Not at all what I expected!  I didn't buy the car from any small used car lot.  I have higher expectations from an official BMW dealer.< /Review>

I brought my wife's vehicle to this location for service.  While most of it was routine service, the front end was making scraping noises.  I believed it to be brakes, which for a 2 year old vehicle with only 16K miles on it seemed out of the normal life of brakes.
The service advisor [Jesse, he was great, a total 10 in our book] called and advised we needed a complete front end brake job, pads, rotors, sensors, and whatever else they do for $1100.  WOW, not his fault the price is what it is, but, for a "brand" that is supposedly high end, this is low end equipment if it only lasts 16k miles.
I called twice to the service manager "Henry", who never called me back, he had "Darin" call my wife.  Wow, there is great customer service, can't return a phone call.  We finally were able to connect with "Darin", after I picked up the vehicle.  He said it's driving patterns and some other lame excuses for why a car of this price and calibre, would need an $1100 brake job.  Plus, of the 16K miles, we only put on 13500, because it was a former loaner vehicle that was taken out of service at 2500 miles.  While I know maybe some of the courtesy loaner drivers may ride the brakes, my wife does not.
So, we were offered the opportunity to purchase the next step warranty for $800, yes a $300 savings, oh, and if the back brakes go out, which they said probably weren't far behind, would be covered.
So my wifes experience with her desire to have a BMW diminished and the obvious quality not there, her next vehicle, [next year] won't be a BMW.
We would not recommend this dealership on their customer service, [other than Jesse], to anyone, and certainly DON"T BUY BMW's.
I think that stands for "buy more warranty's"!< /Review>

Orson Van Gay! If you're in the market for a BMW, which I wasn't, or you see a used car you like in their inventory, which I did, you want to work with Orson. He listens to what you say and hears what you mean. He is a different kind of car salesman! I recommend buying your next vehicle from Orson.

I was searching online for days for my perfect used Lexus RX350 and had seen a couple at other dealerships just to be given lies and the run around at our appointments there. I found a 2011 RX350 at Valencia BMW so to avoid the planned games and sales gimmicks, decided to just drive in and surprise them. Orson met us at the door. He was more interested in meeting my wife and I then getting to business on a car and when we told him we were looking for a specific car from their website he knew exactly which one it was. Orson is very knowledgeable about the vehicles and made the buying process painless. I really appreciate that he did not try to push us into a new car, or even one different than we wanted. When we decided we wanted to buy the car, he had the paperwork drawn up by Mack and set up a wash and fuel up while we waited in the lobby. We walked in at 11am, test drove the car and signed papers and were out by 3 with our new used car and have loved every moment since we walked on the car lot up to today and counting. Thank you Orson, we love our car.</Review>

<Time>1557775011175< /Time><review>My experience with BMW was underwhelming at best.  My 2018 X5 broke down 60 miles from Valencia. I had to get the SUV towed to the dealership. I contacted the dealership, because I knew that I would not arrive by the time the service department closed. My goal was to pick up a loaner because BMW emergency roadside said that the car needed extensive work.  The front desk person, was useless.  She could not get a service person to talk to me, she said I would have to deal with it in the morning. I explained that i live 45 miles from the dealership.  She said she could not help me.

I woke up the next morning to see that I had received no messages from the service department.  I left my keys overnight, it is a bit disconcerting that there was no acknowledgement that they had my car and were reviewing the car.  I had to leave a few messages until my service rep called me back.  He said that my car needed a new fuel pump (a bummer for a one year old car) and that i would have to leave it for a week. He said that I had to come back to the dealer in order to get a loaner.  And the kicker, I would have to pay for the uber.

Finally, my car was ready.  I called ahead (remember I had 45 miles to drive) and asked if my SUV would be ready to go.  The same front desk person as before, said she would.  And, of course it was not ready and it was dirty.  They had to wash it, which took another 20 minutes.

I am leaving out having to call multiple times for updates etc... I will say that my car is now running. That is important.

In summary, you should have a game plan for cars delivered after service hours. You can coordinate with sales to have a loaner available.  Or, be willing to cover the cost of an uber ride back to the dealership.  If someone leaves a car overnight, have the assigned service person call or text first thing in the morning.    Finally, if someone asks for your car to be ready when you get there, then act accordingly.

BMW emergency roadside was not helpful either. They would only tow me to Valencia, they would not tow me to Santa Monica. They said i could pay what would equal $250.00.  At the time I assumed Valencia would allow me to rent a car locally.  I did not expect to have to drive bck there.

Overall, the repairman did his job, the rest did not.</review></record>

<Review>Don't be fooled you can get the same deal on any BMW no matter where you go. When leased my car, I was sold on how impressive the service dept at Valencia BMW you was. I was guaranteed flat bed pick up to my home or office wherever, a loaner car whatever I needed all I had to do was call and schedule the service.

<Review>Interestingly enough, I was speaking to a coworker yesterday, who also owns a BMW, and asked him where he had his service done. He mentioned Valencia BMW, we both gave each other that acknowledging frown and proceeded to rant about how poor this dealership is in regards to it's service department. I'm sorry, I wish I had better things to say, but the Valencia BMW service and parts departments have a lot of work to do to even come close to the customer service I commonly experience at Honda, Fiat, VW or even Ford.

Based on my past visits to your service department, I find the Valencia BMW staff indifferent and inattentive, everyone seems like they're just going through the motions. During my most recent visit, while waiting to drop off my car, someone came in who appeared to have worked at this location before and the friendly attention he received was more in line of what your paying customers should receive.

And the wait times, dropping off or picking up, are far too long, even when you have a scheduled appointment. This isn't the first time I've had to wait this long, it happens every time. During my most recent service appointment, I had a 5:40pm scheduled drop-off, I arrived and checked-in early and still wasn't seen by the service advisor until almost 6:10pm.

Then when I came to pick up the car the next day, the porter took almost 30 minutes to bring my car up to the front, even though the waiting room seemed virtually empty. To further my frustration, the porter also left some nice, greasy black streaks on my beige floor mats! Do you folks use any of the paper floor covers that other car dealerships use to protect their customer's interiors?

Adding to this wonderful experience, I walked into the parts departments and a bell rang to alert the staff that there was someone up front waiting to purchase some genuine BMW parts. I stood in a completely empty room for over 10 minutes. I finally went back to the entrance door, opened and closed several times get the door bell to ring a few times before someone finally came out to help me.

Honda, VW, Fiat and Ford parts departments allow me to pay for and pick up my parts at the same desk. You guys might want to check out your competition. It wasn't the best or the worst experience. It was a long distance deal- I bought the car sight un-seen and worked the deal virtually. I had never done that before and I fully expected it would be different, but figured the dealership would work to help me understand the process. They did, but it was challenging. I never felt like my salesman had any interest in the deal, or making it work for me,  or had any enthusiasm for helping me understand the long distance process - he just kept saying "it'll take a while." - Which is fine, I just felt that he could have/should have proactively given me an idea of what it would take, what he would do, and what to expect - which is good customer service. Instead, I just asked a ton of questions and felt they were met with short answers that weren't overly helpful. It was just a lack of explanation in general with the deal that was frustrating. Autonation, offers a 3 day 250-mile warranty that was voided on my deal - likely (I can only assume) because it was a long distance deal. Again, that's not a problem, I had no intentions of returning, but that's an important issue that probably should have been explained. The finance guy was totally rude, I left him a message declining his added products and never got a call back to confirm that the paperwork was on the way - which I think is just rude. There was some issue with the temporary permits - admittedly, I'm not totally clear on what happened, but the optics of it appeared that my salesman dropped the ball and then tried to blame it on someone else when I was frustrated because I couldn't drive the car. Again, it may have just been optics but it felt off. Ultimately, the deal got done, I got the car, and nothing went catastrophically wrong - it was just a general lack of interest by the salesman, I found it odd that he never picked up the phone and called me and last, but not least, that he never bothered to thank me for my business. I know it was long distance and we never met, but I still had a choice of where to go and I chose here - so some appreciation by way of a simple "thank you for doing business with us" - doesn't seem to be an unreasonable ask. In the end I have a great car and I'm glad about that. Like I said, it wasn't worst, but it was far from the best (which is somewhat expected from a BMW dealer).<//text>

<Text>I went in to purchase a used Lexus RX350 for my daughter.  I was assured that this used vehicle went through a comprehensive 150 point inspection.  My wife encouraged me to buy our used car from a "reputable" dealer convincing me that they would not cheat us, but instead be safer to buy a used car from them then from a small dealer or private party.  WRONG!!!

I took in the used Lexus we purchased from Valencia BMW (the car that was supposed to be inspected by professionals at Valencia BMW) into my local Lexus dealership the next day for routine maintenance, and to my shock given estimates for over $4000 in critical repairs!!!

I should have known when the first thing they listed was new battery because the battery cover to the resoivoir on top was missing.  Obviously, they can't get a cover to match, but you would think that when VBMW listed that they checked the battery, they would have listed this obvious missing piece....or maybe they did not check the battery at all.  Anyway, Lexus service department says I have: leaking transmission O-ring, torn control arm bushings, leaking steering rack which means complete rack replacement and alignment, leaking front light housing.

Should any of these been caught at inspection????? Maybe??? Maybe not???

The point is that when I called the next day to explain the situation to my salesman Willie, he essentially says sorry, the car is sold AS IS!  Nothing he can do and that I should complain to the used car manager.  He did not even offer to talk to the manager on by behalf....just sorry nothing we can do, out of luck, the car is as is.  Don't remind me that it is as is...I f&$@ing know that!!!  I get it...you got your money.

I don't know cars, but I trust that when Valencia BMW "says" that they checked it, I believe them.

My mistake!

At the end of the day, Valencia BMW DID NOTHING to try to make things right with me, not even a follow-up call after I communicated my issue to Willie my salesman.  It's all on them now.

I am now going to drive past this dealership to another dealership to get my maintenance done. I do not feel like Valencia BMW has the same customer service I have grown accustom to.<//Review>

< text>
This past Saturday (04/28/2018), we stopped by Valencia BMW to look at a used Suburban.  We took it for a test drive, and told the sales guy we still had a couple of more vehicles to check out before we made a decision.  My husband called Sathy, our sales guy that same night (Saturday) and made an offer on the vehicle.  He said he would call us back in the morning after speaking with his manager.  We waited around for the call on Sunday morning and finally decided to just drive up there as we intended to buy the vehicle anyways.  Our sales guy from the previous day was there and we spoke to him for a bit before his sales manager, Ryan Annett came out.  Now, we were just trying to get the best price we could on this used vehicle but apparently, Autonation does not negotiate with their pricing.  The sales manager made sure to keep pointing this out and said that‚Äôs the way it is and there is nothing they can do about it.  Only corporate could change it.  He had all but a couple of minutes for us and then just walked away.  We told our sales guy we would discuss this privately for a few minutes (in the car) about it and would let him know.  Five minutes later, we decide to buy the vehicle and went inside to look for Sathy.  We sat in their lobby for about 5 minutes before Sathy finally showed up.  We told him we wanted the vehicle and asked if it could be detailed.  He left to speak with his sales manager for what seemed like 10 minutes.  When he finally came back, he brought his sales manager with him, Ryan.  Ryan then proceeds to tell us that they cannot sell us the vehicle anymore because someone reserved it online.  He said that person would be coming in at 7pm that night and we would have to wait till after to hear back from them if it was sold or not.  Then we were just sent on our way.  We were there on Saturday to look at the vehicle, returned on Sunday to buy the vehicle, and now Ryan tells us that they have to give an opportunity to the person who placed it on hold to look at the vehicle?!  We are in disbelief.  We are standing inside the showroom, ready to buy the vehicle but now we cannot because someone has reserved it.  Ryan says there is nothing they can do but they would call us in the evening if the vehicle does not sell.  I could not believe they turned us away because they had someone else who was interested in the vehicle.  I‚Äôm sure they would not have done this to us if were buying a 60k BMW.  I have never been so insulted or embarrassed in my life.  We had cash on hand, ready to buy the vehicle but Ryan used the excuse that someone else reserved the vehicle while we were there so now we cannot buy it.  We never received a call later that evening or even Monday morning to let us know if it sold or not.  A courtesy phone call would have been nice.  It is Tuesday morning and we are still waiting to hear back.  Talk about lousy customer service.  Before all this went down, I should mention what I observed between their staff.  While my husband and I were outside discussing the vehicle, a sales girl walked out of the office.  She began to speak to another employee (male) as he was walking towards her and he flat out passed right by her and ignored her.  He continued on his way towards the office and she turned back and asked him if he was going to help her of if she should ask anyone else.  Again, he ignored her and went into the office.  She soon followed him in and was walking behind him talking to him and he did not acknowledge her.  What kind of business are you running Mr. Coia?  Your employees seem hostile towards each other.  That explains why your sales manager had no time to waste on us.  No respect for each other or customers who are not buying high end vehicles.</text>

<user_id>115455382982587856789</user_id><Date>1521922263495</Date>< review>
Oh my gosh where to begin. Well we just purchased a CPO X5 2 weeks ago. Our salesperson Madison was excellent. She is a very lovely young lady and was very pleasant to work with. The finance guy on the other hand was not so great so after 5 hours after sitting at the  dealership feeling like our heads were going to explode we finally got to leave with our 2013 X5. When we got to run the car on the freeway i knew that something was off on the alignment. I checked our paperwork and on their CPO checklist it stated that it was good but I took it to our local BMW dealership 2 days after purchase. They checked the alignment and it failed and so we ended up paying $265 to get it done. We contacted the sales manager at Valencia BMW and he said he would reimburse us for the cost. I thought wow thats nice but we still haven't seen anything so I'm not banking on it.

Then today i finally took the car in to get it washed (put it off due to the recent rain) and noticed that the passager side back door had scratches on the door. They took a closer look and told me the car had bondo on it and a poor paint job. From there I went to a local autobody shop to get a more accurate opinion and they confirmed that the bondo is starting to crack and would need to repair and repaint it approximately $800 to $1000.

So long story short I'm extremly disappointed. I know that we purchased a used car and I don't expect perfection however when I think of BMW CPO I think quality and that wasn't what we got. The people at Valencia BMW are very nice (with maybe the exception of the finance guy) but I do feel bamboozled. I would say if you go there please just really examine the vehicle, take your time and look at everything so that you don't end up regretting your purchase.< /review>

I live in Los Angeles, and the ride out to Valencia BMW was well worth it.  No one in my research could touch their offers nor had as wide a selection of cars with various options as Valencia.

My research consisted of emailing and messaging every BMW and Audi dealership around Los Angeles. Messaging all the way down to Long Beach and as far east as Riverside.  I wanted to find the best deal on a 2017/2018 BMW 330e lease or a 2017/2018 Audi E-Tron with the options to fit my budget.

Yliana Fetterolf at Valencia was extremely professional, informative and patient throughout the entire finding/negotiating/buying experience.  She would consistently get back to me in a timely fashion (either email or phone) and show me different cars within my budget.  She was never pushy and made me feel confident that Valencia BMW was the place I'd be buying my car from.  I can't recommend her enough to anyone looking at buying or leasing a BMW.

I couldn't be more happy with the deal Valencia gave me on a 2018, 330e lease, no other dealership could come close. Yliana was completely awesome and made me feel comfortable the entire way.  Not only did she do everything in her power to find me the right 330e to fit within my budget but she also drove the car to me.

< Review>
I leased a 2013 X5 from this place. On the test drive of the X5 the car died and we had to be picked up(not out of gas). My wife really wanted an X5 so we decided to go ahead and get a different X5. The buying portion was pretty good.

When it comes to service....STAY AWAY. I've had on multiple occasions times where the service folks would not call back or give you updates on your car. I would come in early as possible(7am) for the regular oil change and I would not get the car until 4-5 in the evening JUST FOR AN OIL CHANGE. One time they surprisingly called me and told me my car was ready and was being washed. So I got dropped off at the service department only to wait for an hour and 20 min, after being told multiple times that my car was being washed. At this point it was taking so long I thought I was getting a detail LOL. When the car finally came out I was just going to hop in and leave, but something told me to do a walk around and boom this is when I saw a big yellow mark/scratch on the front corner bumper. I asked the person that brought the car up and he said "Oh it came in like that" which is a lie because the service adviser does a walk around with the customer(me) when you drop the car off and it was not there, I would have noticed. I told the service adviser and he had no words. They took it back and said they would fix it which they did. Then I started wondering how that would happen and what yellow car did they hit?? Then I noticed that the car wash has 2 yellow poles right in front of it......Lightbulb goes on, the poor pole has been hit so many times, you can see all the markings and paint scraped on it from the service guys hitting it with peoples cars. They had the nerve to blame me saying I brought it in like that.

I was warned by multiple friends that live in the area to avoid this place but i'm stubborn I guess.

A couple of weeks ago my wife and I went to inquire about buying out our lease, but we were told that we couldn't do to a big recall, OK fair enough, but we didn't want to get another car from there. We were hassled by the sales shark\guy to look at a new model which we said no thank you, then he proceeded to ask us to stay for hot dogs and drinks to which we politely declined and started walking away, when we were almost to our car he said well we have "Fried Chicken and Watermelon if you want!!". At the time I didn't think anything of it until I was down the street already, my wife said "did he just offer us Fried Chicken and watermelon?" I said yes he did. I was so close to turning around and going back to see if they actually had it so I could call his bluff. Being African American I was insulted at the petty attempt of a stereotype joke that it was best for him that I did not turn around. Instead they can take this car back and be done with me forever. Never again will I drop another dime here after I return this vehicle. BMW Valencia you should be ashamed.< /Review>

<rate>1< /rate>< text>
I bought a vehicle here at the beginning of November 2013. To keep things short and sweet I had nothing but a horrible time since the night I walked in there and made the purchase. First, always make sure you have acquired financing before leaving with the vehicle. I asked the salesman while my friend was with me multiple times about this and my concern with taking the car near closing on a Saturday evening. I was assured there were no issues after the credit check and within 3 days I was asked to pony up more cash for the deal to go through.  In the end it worked out, but please do not make my mistake. Verify with BMW Financial before you even get the seat and mirrors where you want them.

The night I purchased the car I also noticed some marks on the rear of the seats, bright red multiple locations. Since it has an Ivory interior it is definitely noticeable and the salesman asked if it would be possible to contact him during the week and setup an appointment to have this taken care of. I agreed since it was already closing time and believed him that this would be taken care of. A month has passed and nothing. No email response no phone calls returned.  This was also the theme when I was initially asked to put more down for the financing to work....no email response no phone calls returned until finally a resolution later in the week when I was contacted by the Finance Director. So if you could imagine selling your other vehicle the day after the purchase, only to find out there is a problem with financing....then no communication for days on where everything stands. I was a little on edge.

Last thing is when I received my plates from the DMV and prompted me to write this review. I went to install them and the front and rear nut plates were stripped down to nothing because the person that installed the dealer plates had used machine screws to hold everything in place. Front license plate holder was only being held in by one machine screw and another one just long enough to keep the entire bracket in place. What if this was your wife's brand new car and she had the kids with her driving down our already terrible So Cal roads, only to have a tire blow out by 3 inch long machine screws from a front license plate bracket that could not be held in place on your MSRP 63,000 vehicle.

Contacted BMW North America, though sympathetic even after sending pics, still nothing regarding a resolution. I will end up just paying an upholstery expert to help get the marks out. Found a way to rig the plates in place, "rig - To make or construct in haste or in a makeshift manner".

Also no email from either the dealer or BMW on my experience. I have heard this is a regular feedback requested from buyers by both parties.

Be cautious, I know a salesman will promise you the world to get you off the lot in one of their cars regardless of manufacture, but I did not expect this for my first and probably last BMW purchase.</text>

< Review>
I called Valencia BMW on the 27th of October and spoke to Hiten Advani about a used car I was interested in on the lot.  He answered all of the questions I asked with complete truthfulness.  To me it was evident in his voice and demeanor.  I told him of my situation of being 4 hours north of Valencia and that I could not get there until the 29th a Saturday.  I explained that I would fly to Burbank and arrive at the airport at 9am and I asked what transportation was available to get to the dealership and if he could hold the car for me. He said he could hold for 48 hours with a bankcard deposit and offered to pick me up at the airport on his way to work.  What more could I ask for?  The deal was done!

I made my flight reservation and gave Hiten the flight number and used the bankcard hold system provided by the dealership.  We exchanged email & phone/text info.  I arrived on time in Burbank and texted Hiten immediately.  Walked out of the airport and he was there in minutes.  We both saw each other easily and were on our way to the dealership asap.

Upon arrival he drove me up to the vehicle and we checked it out visually and took a test drive.  All was exactly as described!  And I had met a true gentleman that I would recommend to anyone.  This man knows what he is doing and will help you meet your needs.  I will be back!  Thank you Hiten and Valencia BMW for having good people like him to help someone find their car.

<user_id>109223481181406158818</user_id><user_name>Ryan Hanlon</user_name>< Time>
1402610627156</Time>
<rate>5</rate>< review>
I have been shopping for a new "fun" car for some time and ran thru the whole gamut of sport / luxury sedans.  After driving various cars, and a number of BMW models, I decided that I wanted a new or very low mile 550i.

I had previously visited Valencia BMW in the past 6 months when casually looking at several other cars, and both of my previous visits had been pleasant and stress free.  So, after shopping and driving a couple local dealers near my home in Ventura, I went out to visit Valencia BMW.

The salesman I worked with, Robert Grass, a longtime BMW enthusiast, was professional, upbeat and very knowledgeable.  He found a perfect used 2014 550i for me with very low miles, gave an excellent overview of the car and after taking a drive, we worked out our deal.  They were very efficient and having shopped around considerably, they were both easy to deal with and competitively priced. I could not have been happier with the car and after filling out a credit application and various paperwork, was quickly moved into their Finance office.

The Finance director, Amir Mansour, was a pleasure to work with as well.  He was fast with all of the DMV paperwork and it was easy to see why he had been with the company for 15 years as he was very good at his job. On the way out, I was introduced to Mr. Gary Pilikyan, the General Manager.  He was a very nice man and I complimented him on how well run and professional his store was.

After I had taken delivery of the car, another gentleman spent about 25 minutes teaching me about all the technology (I am a first time BMW owner) and making sure I was comfortable with leaving in my new vehicle.  And finally, they confirmed my home address so that they could have my SUV dropped off at my house the next day, which eliminated me having to drive back with someone to get it.

In summary, I was floored by the professionalism and courtesy I experienced from Valencia BMW.  I do not casually give out glowing recommendations so I can promise you this, they absolutely earned all of the accolades I'm giving them.

And needless to say, I plan to come back and buy more cars from them in the future..<//review>

My husband and I purchased a 335i GT last Thursday after having email and phone correspondence with Lillian. I am very happy with my car and my experience with Lillian, whom I can describe as one of the most sincerest, down to earth car salesperson I have ever had the pleasure to deal with. We actually walked away from several dealerships (BMW, Lexus to be exact, in Orange County) during the previous week before finding Lilli. Those salesmen were arrogant and unwilling to work within our budget; literally telling us to accept their MSRP price or forget it. We already had our financing and minds made up as to what we wanted and Lilli worked hard to stay in touch and find the car within our budget. In fact, she exceeded our expectations on the day we came to purchase.
I highly recommend Lillian Rodriquez as someone who will work hard for you with honesty and integrity. I have already told many friends and family members about her and this dealership.< /text>
